To set CSS for a widget.

QPushButton {
    color: red;
}

To set CSS for a particular widget, you must set both the ObjectName and possibly, on
certain platforms, the AccessibleName.

QPushButton#MyPushButtonName {
    color: red;
}

For further information read docs at http://doc.qt.io/qt-4.8/stylesheet-syntax.html
Nice tutorial at http://thesmithfam.org/blog/2009/09/10/qt-stylesheets-tutorial/


QLineEdit {
    padding: 1px;
    border-style: solid;
    border: 2px solid gray;
    border-radius: 8px;
}

QPushButton {
    color: white;
    background-color: QLinearGradient( x1: 0, y1: 0, x2: 0, y2: 1, stop: 0 #88d, stop: 0.1 #99e, stop: 0.49 #77c, stop: 0.5 #66b, stop: 1 #77c);
    border-width: 1px;
    border-color: #339;
    border-style: solid;
    border-radius: 7;
    padding: 3px;
    font-size: 10px;
    padding-left: 5px;
    padding-right: 5px;
    min-width: 100px;
    max-width: 200px;
    min-height: 13px;
    max-height: 13px;
}

QPushButton#executeButton {
    background-color: #FFFFFF;
}

QPushButton#executeButton:pressed {
    background-color: #FFFF00
}

QPushButton#executeButton:hover:!pressed {
    background-color: #DDDDEE
}